wiki.summary: Polo G recruits up and coming Bronx rapper Lil Tjay for the first time on “Pop Out,” where the two rap about their streets ties and rises in fame and popularity. Produced by Iceberg Beatz and JD On Tha Track, the track features a piano and electric guitar-backed instrumental, sharing elements of both melodic trap and Chicago drill. The track received a Gunna and Lil Baby-assisted remix, which appears alongside the original on the Chicago native’s debut studio album, Die A Legend. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: Polo G recruits up and coming Bronx rapper Lil Tjay for the first time on “Pop Out,” where the two rap about their streets ties and rises in fame and popularity. Produced by Iceberg Beatz and JD On Tha Track, the track features a piano and electric guitar-backed instrumental, sharing elements of both melodic trap and Chicago drill. The track received a Gunna and Lil Baby-assisted remix, which appears alongside the original on the Chicago native’s debut studio album, Die A Legend. The monumental track for Polo peaked at #11 on the Billboard Hot 100 and is certified 6x Multi-Platinum by the RIAA. Read more on Last.fm.
